## 💡 Tips for AI Assistants

1. **Always check SDLC 4.4 readiness & compliance** before suggesting changes
2. **Follow existing patterns** in the codebase
3. **Update documentation** when making changes
4. **Consider performance** implications with <50ms target
5. **Think about security** for every change
6. **Write tests** for new functionality including cross-module tests
7. **Use meaningful** variable and function names
8. **Keep it simple** - avoid over-engineering
9. **Ask for clarification** when requirements are unclear
10. **Validate assumptions** before implementation
11. **Apply System Thinking** - consider cross-module impact
12. **Validate dependencies** - check all module relationships
13. **Test integrations** - ensure cross-module communication
14. **Monitor integrity metrics** - continuity, drift anomalies, readiness index
15. **Coordinate AI+Human teams** - share governance telemetry context
16. **Enforce Design-First** - architecture hash recorded before code
17. **Leverage Claude Code roles** - assign role prompts aligned with gating mode
18. **Surface governance deltas** - annotate continuity & KPI impact in reasoning

